  "creative-fatigue-meta-ads": {
    title: "How to Detect Creative Fatigue in Meta Ads Before It Kills Your ROAS",
    description: "Creative fatigue is the #1 silent killer of Meta Ads performance. Learn the exact signals, the timeline, and the process for detecting fatigue early — before CPM spikes and ROAS collapses.",
    category: "Performance",
    readTime: "7 min",
    date: "March 2026",
    author: "AdBrief Team",
    authorRole: "Performance Intelligence",
    keywords: ["creative fatigue meta ads", "ad creative fatigue", "facebook ads creative fatigue", "meta ads performance decline", "ad frequency fatigue", "refresh ad creative"],
    content: [
      "## The Problem Nobody Talks About Until It's Too Late",
      "Creative fatigue is the most common cause of ROAS decline in Meta Ads accounts — and most media buyers don't catch it until the damage is done. By the time CPM has spiked 40% and CTR has halved, you've already wasted a week's budget on exhausted creative.",
      "The good news: creative fatigue has predictable early warning signals. Catching them a week early is the difference between a proactive creative refresh and an emergency campaign pause.",
      "## What Creative Fatigue Actually Is",
      "Creative fatigue doesn't mean your ad is bad. It means the algorithm has shown your ad to everyone in your target audience who was likely to respond positively. The remaining audience has either seen it too many times, or they're the segment that was never going to click.",
      "Meta's algorithm is optimizing for engagement. When engagement signals weaken, it either raises CPM to maintain delivery or reduces spend automatically. Both outcomes hurt ROAS.",
      "## The Fatigue Timeline on Meta",
      "Based on aggregate performance data, most prospecting creatives on Meta follow a predictable arc: Days 1-7 are the learning and scaling phase where CPM stabilizes and CTR peaks. Days 8-14 are the performance peak — best ROAS, lowest CPM, highest hook rate. Days 15-21 are early decline — frequency starts rising, CTR starts dipping. Day 21+ is the fatigue zone — CPM spikes, CTR collapses, ROAS drops.",
      "The key insight: you should be launching new creative at day 10-14, not waiting for day 21+ to react.",
      "## The 4 Early Warning Signals",
      "**Signal 1: Frequency above 2.5 for cold audiences.** When your prospecting campaigns hit frequency 2.5+, you're starting to repeat to the same people. Engagement typically drops within 3-5 days of crossing this threshold.",
      "**Signal 2: Hook rate declining week-over-week.** Hook rate measures what percentage of people who see your ad watch the first 3 seconds. A declining hook rate means your opening is losing its novelty — audiences have seen it.",
      "**Signal 3: CPM rising while impressions are flat.** If Meta is charging you more per thousand impressions but your reach isn't growing, the algorithm is working harder to find willing viewers — a classic early fatigue signal.",
      "**Signal 4: CTR declining despite stable targeting.** If nothing changed in your targeting or bidding but CTR dropped 20%+ week-over-week, your creative is losing effectiveness.",
      "## What Most Teams Get Wrong",
      "The most common mistake is pausing fatigued ads instead of replacing them. Pausing creates a gap in learning data and forces the algorithm to restart optimization on the new creative from scratch. The better approach is launching new creative into the same ad set while letting fatigued ads wind down naturally.",
      "The second most common mistake is refreshing creative too aggressively. Launching 10 new ads at once fragments your budget and learning data. Launch 2-3 new variations at a time, let the algorithm identify a winner, then scale that winner.",
      "## How AdBrief Catches Fatigue Early",
      "AdBrief connects directly to your Meta Ads account and monitors creative performance continuously. Instead of manually checking frequency, hook rate, and CTR trends across every active ad, you ask: 'Which of my ads are showing fatigue signals?' and get a plain-English answer with the specific ads, the signals they're showing, and what to brief next.",
      "The creative brief generation is built directly from your account's historical winners — so the replacement creative has a higher baseline probability of performing.",
      "Try AdBrief free for 1 day on any plan. Connect your Meta account and ask about creative fatigue in your active campaigns right now.",
    ],
  },

