      "## The Worst Feeling in Performance Marketing",
      "You check your dashboard on Monday morning and ROAS is down 40% from last week. Spend is the same. Budget hasn't changed. But something broke over the weekend — and you have no idea what.",
      "This guide walks through every real cause of a sudden ROAS drop on Meta Ads, in order of likelihood, with the exact signals to look for and what to do about each one.",
      "## The 6 Real Causes of a Sudden ROAS Drop",
      "### 1. Creative Fatigue (Most Common — 60% of Cases)",
      "Creative fatigue happens when your audience has seen your ads enough times that engagement drops. The symptoms are specific: CPM rises, CTR falls, but your audience size and targeting haven't changed.",
      "How to confirm it: Check your frequency metric. If your top ad sets are hitting frequency above 3.0 for cold audiences or above 5.0 for warm, fatigue is the primary driver. Cross-reference with hook rate — if the first 3-second view rate has dropped more than 20% week-over-week, the hook is burned.",
      "The fix: Rotate creative immediately. Don't tweak existing ads — launch fresh creative with different hooks. The winning pattern from your best-performing ads (same CTA, different opening) typically rescues ROAS within 3-5 days.",
      "### 2. Audience Saturation",
      "If you've been running the same campaign to the same audience for 30+ days without expanding, you've reached most of the people worth reaching. New impressions go to lower-quality segments of the audience.",
      "How to confirm it: Your reach is growing slowly but your CPM is accelerating. The audience saturation percentage in Audience Insights will show above 70%.",
      "The fix: Expand lookalike percentages (1% → 2-3%), introduce new interest stacks, or move budget to broader audiences temporarily while you build new custom audiences.",
      "### 3. iOS / Attribution Window Shifts",
      "Attribution windows on Meta can shift without you changing anything — iOS updates, browser privacy changes, and Meta's own algorithm adjustments can cause the same revenue to be attributed differently.",
      "How to confirm it: Check your actual revenue in your store or payment processor against what Meta is reporting. If the gap has widened, it's an attribution issue, not a performance issue.",
      "The fix: Switch your reporting window to 7-day click, 1-day view for consistency. Use UTM parameters and server-side events to cross-reference Meta data with ground truth.",
      "### 4. Competition Spike (Seasonal or Market)",
      "Other advertisers bidding in your auction increase CPMs for everyone. This happens during major sales events, product launches from competitors, and seasonal peaks (Valentine's Day, Black Friday, etc.).",
      "How to confirm it: Your CPM has spiked but your CTR has stayed roughly the same. This suggests the creative is fine — the audience just costs more to reach.",
      "The fix: Temporary — wait it out if it's seasonal. Structural — if competition has permanently increased in your niche, you need higher-performing creative to maintain your effective CPM at the same cost.",
      "### 5. Landing Page or Funnel Change",
      "Meta's algorithm optimizes for the downstream event you're bidding on — usually purchase or add-to-cart. If something changed in your funnel (slower page load, checkout flow update, offer change), Meta's optimization gets confused.",
      "How to confirm it: Your add-to-cart and initiate-checkout events are stable, but purchase conversion rate has dropped. This localizes the problem to the landing page or checkout.",
      "The fix: Revert any recent funnel changes. A/B test landing page variants. Check page load speed — a 1-second delay in load time reduces conversions by 7%.",
      "### 6. Meta Algorithm Relearning",
      "If you edited a campaign, changed a bid strategy, expanded an audience, or increased budget by more than 20% at once, Meta's algorithm enters a learning phase. During learning, delivery is unstable and performance drops.",
      "How to confirm it: Your campaign shows 'Learning' or 'Learning Limited' status. Performance will be volatile for 7-10 days.",
