      "**1. Pattern interrupt (visual surprise):** Highest hook rate — 35-45% average. An unexpected visual, unusual angle, or disruptive first frame that breaks the scroll pattern.",
      "**2. Direct problem statement:** 30-40% average. 'Tired of wasting ad spend on dead creative?' directly addresses the viewer's pain.",
      "**3. Curiosity gap:** 28-38% average. 'Nobody in your industry is doing this yet.' Creates an information gap that compels completion.",
      "**4. Social proof number:** 25-35% average. '47,000 brands cut their CPM with this.' Numbers create credibility and pattern interrupt simultaneously.",
