      "This guide is the systematic recovery plan. Not general advice — a sequenced diagnostic that identifies exactly what broke and how to fix it.",
      "## Phase 1: Confirm the Problem Is Real (Days 1-2)",
      "Before making any changes, confirm the performance drop is real and not a reporting artifact.",
      "**Check attribution:** Pull your actual revenue from your store backend (Shopify, WooCommerce, Stripe) for the same period and compare to what Meta reports. If there's a new gap, you have an attribution issue — not a performance issue. Fix your pixel, server-side events, and reporting windows before changing anything in-account.",
      "**Check seasonality:** Compare this period to the same period last year. Some performance drops are normal seasonal patterns that look like account problems.",
      "**Check external factors:** Price changes, shipping delays, product stockouts, negative reviews — any external factor that reduces conversion rate will look like an ads problem when it isn't.",
      "If the performance drop is real and not explained by attribution or external factors, move to Phase 2.",
      "## Phase 2: Identify Where the Funnel Broke (Days 2-3)",
      "Pull these metrics and find the step with the largest 30-day drop:",
      "CTR → Landing page view rate → Add-to-cart rate → Purchase rate",
      "**CTR dropped most:** Creative problem. Hook has fatigued or lost relevance.",
      "**CTR fine, landing page view rate dropped:** Technical problem between click and page load. Check speed, redirect chains, page errors.",
      "**Landing page views fine, add-to-cart dropped:** Offer or page problem. Something on your landing page lost trust or relevance.",
      "**Add-to-cart fine, purchase rate dropped:** Checkout problem. Review recent checkout changes, payment options, shipping costs.",
      "This funnel analysis tells you exactly where to focus. Don't fix the creative if the problem is in checkout.",
